FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#F5F5DC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubremmin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bremmin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>3/25/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>6:41:32 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.eternusastralis.com/site/logo/ea60x60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">My position on isle seven in Sky</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Quite a few people have been asking me about this recently both in and out of game, and since I'm never one to keep my mouth shut I figured I'd just spell it all out with regards to my point of view.<br>
<br>
I feel personally that it's wrong for anyone who has never seen Isle Six to get a Crown of Elemental Mastery: Air. Its as simple is that. Its recently come to my attention that the people who are currently camped on Isle Seven never plan on leaving, and that furthermore they plan on summoning up every level 46+ magician who is trying to complete their epic quest.<br>
<br>
It is my opinion that you're probably taking advantage of a situation that the officers of EA never intended to create. I don't pretend to read minds, but since I actually know these people as friends and interact with them on a daily basis, I'm willing to wager that this is the case. <br>
<br>
Most everyone I've spoken to on the issue doesn't seem to understand the difference between getting to isle seven on a raid and getting summoned to isle seven whenever they wish. In fact, while engaged in a debate earlier today somebody said that if mages shouldn't be able to randomly appear on isle seven anytime they can pay for coffins, then clerics should have to reserve fire giants on the calendar. I really don't see how the two situations compare.<br>
<br>
I guess what I'm saying is I could be conceivably be convinced to see the point of summoning everyone who's been to isle six and almost made it, or everyone who got to isle seven only to never see a crown, but IMHO summoning every mage on the server is wrong, and it makes me feel bad that I even went up on the original EA raid.<br>
<br>
--Bremmin Ironsoul<br>
Lv 54 Vicar of Brell and super d0rf at large <br>
<br>
