<br>
As a side note, before I begin, you should know that I was invited to the Friday evening raid, and I did attend.  It was not my first trip to Air, but it was my first trip to Isle 7.  I am not aware of plans to indefinitely camp people there, but that doesn't mean it's not the case.  I would have issues, much as your own, if that's true, though.<br>
<br>
For me, what happened specifically on Friday, though, was not much different than doing the zone with more than 24 people (the number of keys available).  Nor did it differ wildly from, on a two day raid, bringing up some higher levels on Day 2, while the under 55 crowd leaves.<br>
<br>
And that was the point of my previous post.<br>
<br>
BTW, for those that don't know me, I'm not a mage.  I went to help someone who asked for my help, and I was happy to do that.  It was a side benefit to me that I got to see Nkiny (for whom I have the greatest respect) get her crown, and well, Petoffen was *almost* speechless - might be a first <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  Truly, I was very happy for them, and delighted to have been there.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CCCCCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvydas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vydas</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>3/25/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>8:17:34 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: My position on isle seven in Sky</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">If the farming of this is the plan, well, that does bother me.  It bothers me in the same way as parking a mage at a rare or particularly difficult or desired spawn and CoH'ing others in would bother me.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#F5F5DC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzukhov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zukhov</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://members.tripod.co.uk/EQZukhov/Zport.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>3/25/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FF0000>10:10:48 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://members.tripod.co.uk/EQZukhov/sigg.jpg width = 178 height = 268></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: My position on isle seven in Sky</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I don't like power leveling or twinking either but it happens all the time and seems to be accepted. I think the idea that you have to achive something yourself in EQ has long gone out of the window.<br>
<br>
If there is an opportunity to exploit people will take it, wether its using a bug to defeat an uber mob or game mechanics to easily get an epic quest piece.<br>
